SIMPLE: acuminate
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acuminate
<hw>A*cu"mi*nate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acuminatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>acuminare</ets> to sharpen, fr.
<ets>acumen</ets>. See <er>Acumen</er>.]</ety> <def>Tapering to a point;
pointed; <as>as, <ex>acuminate</ex> leaves, teeth, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acuminate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Acuminate
<hw>A*cu"mi*nate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To render
sharp or keen.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧To <xex>acuminate</xex>
even despair.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acuminate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Acuminate
<hw>A*cu"mi*nate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To end in, or come to, a
sharp point.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Acuminating</xex> in a cone of
prelacy.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acumination</ent>⟦br⟧
